      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Ah, it sounds like the negative margin on the title might be the culprit, especially since you're seeing it on the iPhone 13 view. Removing the negative margin could either make it worse or better, depending on how the rest of your layout is structured. It's like trying to balance a scale with a mischievous goblin on one side — you just never know what will tip the scales!\n\nTo handle this using Flexbox, you can try adjusting the `align-items` property on the `.product-header` to center the title vertically. This is like giving the title a little nudge to sit right in the middle of the image, rather than being squished by it. Here's how you could adjust your CSS:\n\n```css\n.product-header {\n  display: flex;\n  flex-direction: column;\n  padding: 20px;\n  align-items: center; /* This will center the title vertically */\n}\n```\n\nThis should help keep the title and image in harmony, regardless of the screen size. And remember, when dealing with Flexbox, it's all about finding that perfect balance, just like trying to herd a bunch of mischievous goblins into a pen. Happy coding!",
